    "body": "### Problem\n\nThere is no way to get the time a mark was created.\n\nWhen multiple marks share the same line, it is not possible to reliably prioritize displaying the most recently created one. This is especially important when rendering marks in the signcolumn, where only a single character can be shown (`auto`, `yes:1`).\n\n<img width=\"129\" height=\"103\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/a8d1bdc7-951d-4fca-a655-ad7a8f5f3764\" />\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nA possible solution is to return the mark creation time via the existing `*_get_mark()` functions:\n\n```lua\nnvim_buf_get_mark({buffer}, {name}) -> (row, col, timestamp)\n                                                  ^ New!\nnvim_get_mark({name}, {opts}) -> (row, col, buffer, buffername, timestamp)\n                                                                ^ New!\n```",
